windows activities:
driver.manage().window().maximize(); - maximize window
driver.navigate().to(URL) - navigate to next url - but driver will not wait 
                          - driver.get will wait for the page to load 


**************************************************************************************

Dropdown:
Static dropdown:

Select tag -> create object for select class 
- dropdown cannot be directly selected and it is not visible to selenium
- object for select class is created
- webelement for the dropdown is used in select class
- dropdown can be selected by object.



****************************************************************************************

Synchronization in selenium:

1. Implicit wait:
   -define wait time globally (wait seconds before throwing exception)
   -waits for the element to load
   -one the element is loaded , it will not wait for remaining seconds - it will move to next step
   - Disadvantages: for example if a implicit wait is defined for 15 seconds - and if it fail- it will take 15 seconds
   for us to know that the step is failed

2.Explicit wait:
   - target a specific element
   - it is helpful for performance testing - for duration of seconds
   - 2 different waits Fluentwait and Webdriverwait
   - Webdriverwait -- continuosly monitor
   - Fluentwait -- monitor at regular intervals of time with polling s
   
   
   
3. Thread.sleep
   - it is part of java
   - pause the entire script
   -one the element is loaded , it will wait for remaining seconds - it will not move to next step  
   
 
